The paper discusses the use of machine learning techniques for biometric authentication, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper specifically focuses on the use of artificial neural networks, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The use of biometric data, such as fingerprints, also involves computer vision techniques (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the use of fuzzy extractors, which is a cryptographic technique (cs.CR). Finally, the paper discusses the use of handheld computation devices, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
